    <h2>Quick decision tree</h2>
    <p>Read these in order and stop at the first "yes."</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Are you running ads on Google (AdSense, Ads, or GA4 with Consent Mode v2) and serving EU/UK visitors?</strong> → You need a Google-certified, IAB-validated CMP. <a href="https://www.iubenda.com/" rel="noopener sponsored">iubenda</a> is the clearest fit in this comparison; Osano also qualifies but at 40× the entry price.</li>
      <li><strong>Is your audience 80%+ US, and is your budget under $20/month?</strong> → Start on <a href="https://termly.io/" rel="noopener sponsored">Termly's</a> free tier, upgrade only when you actually need branded banners or multi-language.</li>
      <li><strong>Do you have a named privacy or compliance officer, 5+ properties, and a six-figure regulatory exposure?</strong> → <a href="https://www.osano.com/" rel="noopener sponsored">Osano</a> is built for that role. Its vendor-risk database is genuinely useful at enterprise scale and the No-Fines pledge transfers risk in a way the other two don't.</li>
      <li><strong>None of the above?</strong> → You're a growing SMB with EU + US traffic. <a href="https://www.iubenda.com/" rel="noopener sponsored">iubenda's</a> mid-tier (€19.99/month) is the most defensible default — that's the configuration this site runs on.</li>
    </ol>

